article.description: — Mike Bothwell had a career-high 32 points as Furman beat East Tennessee State 78-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Bothwell leads Furman past E. Tennessee St. 78-66
article.linkText: Bothwell leads Furman past E. Tennessee St. 78-66
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- — Mike Bothwell had a career-high 32 points as Furman beat East Tennessee State 78-66 on Saturday. Alex Hunter had 15 points for Furman (10-3, 4-0 Southern Conference), which earned its fifth consecutive victory. Clay Mounce added 14 points and nine rebounds. Jalen Slawson had 11 points. Serrel Smith had 13 points for the Buccaneers (6-5, 2-1). Vonnie Patterson added 13 points. David Sloan had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
